<!-- About Us -->
<section class="container py-5" id="nosotros" style=" background-color: white;">
<h2 class="text-success mb-4"><i class="bi bi-people"></i> Who are we? And why Biking Clinic?</h2>
<div class="row align-items-center">
<div class="col-md-6 mb-4 mb-md-0 text-center">
<img alt="Project team" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" src="rancho-cacachilas-clinica-ciclismo6.jpg" style="max-height: 400px;"/>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<p>We are Juan David García and Juan Sebastián Figueroa, students of Mechanical Engineering passionate about promoting cycling as an eco-friendly, accessible, and healthy way to get around. Our project, <strong>"Biking Clinic"</strong>, is dedicated to cyclist safety, offering tips and resources to help riders stay protected on the road. Through this initiative, we aim to raise awareness about the importance of caring for the environment while also prioritizing the health and safety of every cyclist. With our technical background, we also understand the mechanics and efficiency behind bicycles, which enhances our commitment to improving the cycling experience for everyone.</p>
<p>By fostering a community that supports cycling, we hope to inspire more people to adopt this sustainable transportation method, making our cities cleaner and healthier places to live.</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<!-- Importance -->
<section class="container py-5 bg-light" id="importancia" style=" background-color: white;">
<h2 class="text-success"><i class="bi bi-heart-pulse"></i> Why is cycling important?</h2>
<div class="row align-items-center">
<div class="col-md-6">
<ul>
<li><strong>Improves health:</strong> reduces the risk of heart disease, diabetes, and obesity by promoting regular physical activity and cardiovascular fitness.</li>
<li><strong>Efficient mobility:</strong> faster and more convenient for short trips in congested urban areas, helping reduce traffic jams and commute times.</li>
<li><strong>No polluting emissions:</strong> cycling produces zero greenhouse gases and helps decrease air pollution, contributing to cleaner, healthier environments.</li>
<li><strong>Affordable and economical:</strong> requires low investment for purchase and maintenance compared to motor vehicles, saving money for individuals and families.</li>
</ul>
<p>Encouraging cycling can also lead to less noise pollution and increased social interaction, enhancing the overall quality of life in communities.</p>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<img alt="Benefits of cycling" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" src="2.jpg" style="max-height: 400px;"/>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<!-- Safety -->
<section class="container py-5" id="seguridad" style=" background-color: white;">
<h2 class="text-success"><i class="bi bi-shield-lock"></i> Cyclist safety measures</h2>
<div class="row align-items-center">
<div class="col-md-6 mb-3 mb-md-0 text-center">
<img alt="Cyclist safety" class="img-fluid rounded shadow w-75" src="Imagen de WhatsApp 2025-05-18 a las 17.54.58_36afa7ec.jpg"/>
</div>
<div class="col-md-6">
<ol>
<li>Always wear a helmet when riding to protect your head in case of falls or collisions.</li>
<li>Check brakes, tires, and lights before every ride to ensure your bike is in good condition.</li>
<li>Wear bright or reflective clothing, especially at night, to increase visibility to motorists.</li>
<li>Use hand signals when turning and obey all traffic rules to communicate your intentions clearly.</li>
<li>Avoid using headphones to stay aware of your surroundings and hear traffic sounds.</li>
</ol>
<p>By following these safety measures, cyclists can significantly reduce the risk of accidents and enjoy a safer riding experience.</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<!-- Driver Considerations -->
<section class="container py-5 bg-light" id="conductores" style=" background-color: white;">
<h2 class="text-success"><i class="bi bi-exclamation-triangle"></i> Considerations for Drivers</h2>
<div class="row align-items-center">
<!-- Text content -->
<div class="col-md-6">
<p>Drivers play a crucial role in protecting cyclists. Awareness and mutual respect can prevent accidents and save lives. Keep these guidelines in mind:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Maintain a safe distance:</strong> Leave at least 1.5 meters when overtaking a cyclist.</li>
<li><strong>Don't honk unnecessarily:</strong> Loud horns can scare cyclists and cause them to lose control.</li>
<li><strong>Check your mirrors:</strong> Especially when turning or opening doors near bike lanes.</li>
<li><strong>Respect bike lanes:</strong> Never block or drive in spaces designated for bicycles.</li>
<li><strong>Be patient:</strong> Cyclists may be slower but have equal rights to use the road.</li>
<li><strong>Drive responsibly:</strong> Stay alert, avoid distractions, and never use your phone while driving.</li>
</ul>
<p>Creating safer roads is everyone's responsibility. Together, we can ensure a secure environment for all road users.</p>
</div>
<!-- Image -->
<div class="col-md-6 text-center">
<img alt="Drivers and cyclists" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" src="conductores-ciclistas.jpg" style="max-height: 500px;width: 100%; object-fit: cover;"/>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<!-- Environment -->
<section class="container py-5 bg-light" id="medioambiente" style=" background-color: white;">
<h2 class="text-success"><i class="bi bi-tree"></i> Cycling and the environment</h2>
<p>A bicycle doesn’t just move you — it moves the world toward a cleaner future. Every kilometer pedaled means fewer CO₂ emissions, less noise, and more livable cities. It’s a practical way to combat climate change in our everyday lives.</p>
<p>Switching to cycling for daily transport reduces dependency on fossil fuels, lowers your carbon footprint, and helps preserve natural resources for future generations.</p>
<div class="text-center">
<img alt="Bike and environment" class="img-fluid rounded shadow mt-3" src="1.jpg" style="max-width: 700px;"/>
</div>
</section>
<!-- Tips -->
<section class="container py-5" id="consejos" style=" background-color: white;">
<h2 class="text-success"><i class="bi bi-lightbulb"></i> Tips for new cyclists</h2>
<ul>
<li>Start with short and safe routes to build confidence and skills gradually.</li>
<li>Get familiar with bike lanes in your city to ensure safer rides and better navigation.</li>
<li>Avoid high-traffic areas until you gain experience and feel comfortable riding in different conditions.</li>
<li>Use a bike that fits your size and riding style (urban, mountain, etc.) to improve comfort and control.</li>
</ul>
<p>Joining local cycling groups or taking beginner classes can also boost your confidence and knowledge.</p>
</section>
